 R←Test_Lamp_002(stopFlag batchFlag);⎕TRAP;md;ns
⍝ Test whether a line that starts with a lamp symbol (`⍝`) does not make it to the output.
 ⎕TRAP←(999 'C' '. ⍝ Deliberate error')(0 'N')
 R←∆Failed

 md←''
 md,←⊂'Para 1'
 md,←⊂''
 md,←⊂'⍝ Will be ignored'
 md,←⊂'Para 2'
 md,←⊂''
 md,←⊂'`⍝` must not be ignored.'
 md,←⊂''
 md,←⊂'Para 3'
 md,←⊂'⍝ This should be ignored, too'
 md,←⊂'End of para 3'
 md,←⊂''
 md,←⊂'* This'
 md,←⊂'* That\'
 md,←⊂'⍝ Comment'

 ns←##.MarkAPL.Init''md
 ns←##.MarkAPL.Process ns

 →PassesIf(⊂'<p>Para 1</p>')∊ns.html
 →PassesIf(⊂'<p>Para 2</p>')∊ns.html
 →PassesIf∨/'<p>Para 3'⍷∊ns.html
 →PassesIf(⊂'<p><code>⍝</code> must not be ignored.</p>')∊ns.html
 →FailsIf∨/'Will be ignored'⍷∊ns.html
 →PassesIf 2=+/'<li>'⍷∊ns.html
 →FailsIf∨/'Comment'⍷∊ns.html

 R←∆OK
